==English==
===Etymology===
From Late Latin ''[[acuminatus]]'', past participle of ''[[acuminare]]''. "to sharpen to a point".

===Pronunciation 1===
* ''[[RP]]:''
** {{IPA|/əˈkjuːmɪnet/}}

====Adjective====
'''acuminate'''
# [[taper|Tapering]] to a [[point]]; [[pointed]]; as, acuminate leaves, teeth, etc.

===Pronunciation 2===
* ''[[RP]]:''
** {{IPA|/əˈkjuːmɪneɪt/}}

====Verb====
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|acuminat|e|}}
# {{transitive}} To render [[sharp]] or [[keen]]; to [[sharpen]].
# {{intransitive}} To [[end]] in or come to a sharp point.

